"Processing\\u2026\",\"submit_button_class\":\"\",\"honeypot\":\"1\",\"ajax_form_submission\":\"0\",\"disabled_entries\":\"0\",\"email\":{\"enable_email_notification\":\"1\",\"connection_1\":{\"connection_name\":\"Wildlife Centre Notification\",\"evf_to_email\":\"{admin_email}\",\"evf_from_name\":\"Dyfi Wildlife Centre\",\"evf_from_email\":\"{admin_email}\",\"evf_reply_to\":\"\",\"evf_email_subject\":\"New Form Entry  - Input for Wildlife Centres\",\"evf_email_message\":\"{all_fields}\"}}},\"structure\":{\"row_1\":{\"grid_1\":[\"3wPXLwVhx6-1\",\"mwWo2jLVP0-2\",\"KQvJo7IJIA-3\"]}}}','Input for Wildlife Centres','','publish','closed','closed','','input-for-wildlife-centres','','','2020-04-03 09:56:07','2020-04-03 08:56:07','',0,'http://users.aber.ac.uk/ydw/dyfiwildlifecentre/?post_type=everest_form&#038;p=293',0,'everest_form','',0),(294,1,'2020-04-03 09:56:33','2020-04-03 08:56:33','[[\"ID\",\"Name (location)\",\"Information \",\"Photos\"],[\"1\",\"Corris\",\"We transported some of the pitch pine timber work from Capel Salem, just a few miles up stream in Corris, to the Dyfi Wildlife Centre.\\n\\nWe will repurpose the magnificent looking pews and other paneling to our own needs - cafe booths, servery counter etc\\n\\nCapel Salem was built in 1851 but, as was typical of many Welsh chapels at the time when more money became available, was given a major overhaul in 1895. The renowned carpenter Dimetris Owen from Llanbrynmair was given the contract to renovate the chapel, including installing a brand new gallery area and pulpit.\",\"<img src=\\\"https://www.dyfiospreyproject.com/sites/default/files/images/_DSC7762.jpeg\\\" width=\\\"200\\\" height=\\\"200\\\" alt=\\\"sample wood from corris, used in dyfi wildlife cafe\\\" class=\\\"alignnone size-medium\\\" />\"],[\"2\",\"Machynlleth\",\"A copper-faced longcase clock made by Machynlleth clockmaker Ezekiel Hughes in 1790\",\"<img src=\\\"https://www.dyfiospreyproject.com/sites/default/files/images/IMG_1727.jpeg\\\" width=\\\"200\\\" height=\\\"220\\\" alt=\\\"picture of machynlleth clock face, gold\\\" class=\\\"alignnone size-medium\\\" />\"],[\"3\",\"Bethesda\",\"They are \'Welsh Heather Blues\', so called because of their colour - a deep blue-to-purple shade. Some say, some of the best slates in the world...\\n\\nThey come from Penrhyn quarry in Bethesda, near Bangor, a quarry that has been going for 500 years and was, in the late 1800s, the largest slate quarry in the world.\",\"<img src=\\\"https://www.dyfiospreyproject.com/sites/default/files/images/_DSC4687.jpg\\\" width=\\\"200\\\" height=\\\"220\\\" alt=\\\"slate picture from Bethesda\\\" class=\\\"alignnone size-medium\\\" />\"],[\"4\",\"Metals\",\"Various metals will form a key feature in the new Dyfi Wildlife Centre. Why? For centuries the hills and mountains around the Dyfi River have been the focus of rampant mining activity. It has all come to an end now, but the landscape our ancestors left behind still bear the hallmarks of their metallurgic activities. Romans mined copper on the north side of the Dyfi and Charles I found great success with silver on the south side, so much so, he moved the Royal Mint from London to Aberystwyth Castle in the 1640s and then even nearer to Cors Dyfi in 1649 \\u2013 the little village of Furnace.\",\"<img src=\\\"http://www.dyfiospreyproject.com/sites/default/files/images/53233386_2384334588461368_3065223863148216320_o.jpg\\\" width=\\\"200\\\" height=\\\"200\\\" class=\\\"alignnone size-medium\\\" />\"]]','history','Any edits you would like to make in Column B,C please change below and click save changes. \n\nFor changes to column D please insert photos into the media section on the dashboard and send an email to admin(ydw@aber.ac.uk) in the admin dashboard menu to get them added to live site. \n\nTo delete entries check the rows corresponding box and then press the delete row button in table manipulation.','publish','closed','closed','','history','','','2020-04-16 11:37:48','2020-04-